msgid "Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization Hardware Requirements Overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "This section outlines the minimum hardware required to install, configure, and operate a Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization environment. To setup a Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization environment it is necessary to have, at least:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "one machine to act as the management server,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "one or more machines to act as virtualization hosts - at least two are required to support migration and power management,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "one or more machines to use as clients for accessing the Administration Portal."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "storage infrastructure provided by <acronym>NFS</acronym>, <acronym> iSCSI</acronym>, <acronym> SAN</acronym>, or local storage."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "The hardware required for each of these systems is further outlined in the following sections. The Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization environment also requires storage infrastructure that is accessible to the virtualization hosts. Storage infrastructure must be accessible using <acronym>NFS</acronym>, <acronym>iSCSI</acronym>, <acronym>FC</acronym>, or locally attached to virtualization hosts. The use of other <acronym>POSIX</acronym> compliant filesystems is also supported."
msgstr ""

